ing: 1 (5 ounce) can Italian tuna packed in olive oil, undrained
1/4 cup crumbled reduced-fat feta cheese, or more to taste
salt and ground black pepper to taste
des: "Light and refreshing tuna salad that can be eaten as a main dish or served with pita chips as an appetizer. For meatier salad, add one more can of undrained tuna. You can also add drained, chopped artichoke hearts."
ins: Stir the tuna, chickpeas, olives, parsley, red onion, lemon juice, and feta cheese together in a bowl. Season with salt and pepper.
